text: Maurice Barry (December 31, 1880 - May 15, 1967) was an American gymnast. He competed in three events at the 1904 Summer Olympics. ==References== Category:1880 births Category:1967 deaths Category:American male artistic gymnasts Category:Olympic gymnasts of the United States Category:Gymnasts at the 1904 Summer Olympics Category:Sportspeople from Indianapolis
